02/11/2003
PODGORICA, Serbia-Montenegro -- Meeting in Podgorica on Friday (31 October), the interior ministers of Albania, Macedonia and Serbia-Montenegro, together with UNMIK representatives, signed a regional agreement on combating organised crime.
The document provides for enhancing mutual co-operation and boosting efforts to stabilise the region.
Jean-Christian Cady, head of the UNMIK police and justice department, described a project to establish a regional centre for protection of victims, together with the Stability Pact for Southeast Europe.
Montenegrin Interior Minister Milan Filipovic also signed bilateral agreements on co-operation with his Albanian counterpart and UNMIK police representatives.
(TV Crna Gora, BBC - 31/10/03)
